    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Jackson Merrill** (72.75) and **Kyle Tucker** (72.04) anchoring our outfield, representing our highest efficiency plays. **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a favorable matchup against Burke, where his platoon advantage and a slow opposing delivery create a high-probability environment for both extra-base hits and a stolen base. Simultaneously, **Kyle Tucker** is primed for production against McGreevy; while the park factor is slightly suppressive, his elite base projection and the pitcher\u2019s skill profile justify his status as our primary offensive engine. **Drake Baldwin** also earns a strong nod (67.34), with his promotion to the #2 hole providing a significant boost to his base output against the southpaw Bernardino.\n\nThe most difficult decision on our bench was leaving **Coby Mayo** (52.17) out of the starting nine. While **Coby Mayo** benefited from a platoon edge against Weathers and the same favorable stolen base environment that boosted **Gunnar Henderson**, the depth of our middle infield and utility spots\u2014specifically the surging **Jacob Wilson** (60.10)\u2014pushed him to the pine. We are keeping a close watch on **Josh Lowe** (49.34), who faces a stern test against McLean; while he retains a platoon advantage, his efficiency score is compressed by the elite expected ERA of his opponent, making him the most volatile piece of our starting rotation. Managers should note that while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (61.13) faces a tough Prielipp, the wind blowing out at the park provides a necessary cushion to keep him in the lineup despite the challenging arm.",
